description:
In this session recorded at Unreal Fest Orlando 2025, Aggressive Performance covers Unreal Editor for Fortnite (UEFN) static level optimizations for base geometry and rendering, with a discussion on when to use features like Hierarchical Level of Detail systems (HLODs), World Partition, Level Streaming, spatial loading, draw distances, and culling.

Learn more about UEFN here: unrealengine.com/uses/uefn-unreal-editor-for-fortnite
